      "steps": [
        "In a bowl, combine all the marinade ingredients with the chicken cubes. Mix well, cover, and refrigerate for at least 3 hours, or preferably overnight.",
        "Preheat oven to 450°F (232°C). Place the marinated chicken on skewers or spread on a baking sheet.",
        "Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and slightly charred. Alternatively, you can grill the chicken on a skillet or air fry at 400F (200C) for 12-15 minutes, flipping halfway through.",
        "While the chicken is baking, prepare the sauce. Heat oil in a large skillet or pot over medium heat. Add chopped onion and cook until golden brown, about 5-7 minutes.",
        "Add ginger-garlic paste and green chilies. Sauté for 1 minute until fragrant.",
        "Add crushed Szechuan peppercorns and dried red chilies. Sauté for another minute.",
        "Stir in tomato passata, water, soy sauce, sugar, garam masala, coriander powder, and cumin powder. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low, cover, and cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
        "Remove from heat and blend the sauce using an immersion blender until smooth. Return the sauce to the skillet.",
        "Stir in heavy cream and butter. Cook for a few more minutes until the butter is melted and the sauce is creamy.",
        "Add salt to taste, and then carefully stir in the baked chicken tikka. Simmer for 2-3 minutes, allowing the chicken to absorb the sauce.",
        "Stir in the crushed kasuri methi.",
        "Garnish with fresh cilantro. Serve hot with basmati rice or naan."
      ],
      "prep_time_minutes": 20,
